---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Thirty years across military operations, physical security, ICS/OT cybersecurity, and AI — and the translation between them."
	pubDate={new Date('July 11 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		I'm Daniel. For thirty years I've worked across the domains that protecting critical
		infrastructure actually demands — military operations, physical security, ICS/OT
		cybersecurity, and now AI. Most careers go deep in one. I've spent mine learning to
		translate between them.
	</p>

	<p>
		My work sits where operational technology meets AI: the plant floors, utilities, and
		regulated manufacturing that society quietly runs on — now being handed tools nobody has
		taught them to trust, or to question. These are places where a security decision is also a
		safety decision, a compliance decision, and a production decision, all at once. IEC 62443.
		NIS2. The EU AI Act. And a system that can't simply be switched off because a vendor
		shipped a patch.
	</p>

	<p>
		This is where I think it through in public. What AI can actually do, what an OT environment
		will actually tolerate, and what the people accountable for these systems actually need to
		decide — capability, constraint, and consequence, held in the same frame.
	</p>

	<p>
		I'm not here to build an audience. I'm writing toward a smaller number of people doing
		serious work at the same intersection. If that's you, get in touch.
	</p>
</Layout>
